Hi Everyone, 

Is it possible to automatically add all the tests of a test class to a suite
without using &#39;suite.addTestSuite(MyTest.class)&#39;?

I have a test class that can test a number of classes from the same
hierarchy.  Let&#39;s say for arguments sake that I have created two child
classes (ChildA and ChildB) of type JTextComponent and both of them override
a number of methods such as setText.  I have a number of tests that test the
newly overridden methods.  I have created a constructor for the class that
looks something like this:

	public MyTest(String name, JTextComponent component)
	{
		super(name);
		this.component = component;
	}	

My problem is this: I want to run this test twice, once for childA and once
for childB.  But I don&#39;t want to type in the tests individually e.g.

	public class MyTestClient
	{
		public static Test suite()
		{
			TestSuite suite = new TestSuite();

			suite.addTest(new MyTest(&quot;test1&quot;, new ChildA()));
			suite.addTest(new MyTest(&quot;test2&quot;, new ChildA()));
			suite.addTest(new MyTest(&quot;test3&quot;, new ChildA()));
			........
			suite.addTest(new MyTest(&quot;testN&quot;, new ChildA()));

			// Then the same for childB			
			suite.addTest(new MyTest(&quot;test1&quot;, new ChildB()));
			suite.addTest(new MyTest(&quot;test2&quot;, new ChildB()));
			suite.addTest(new MyTest(&quot;test3&quot;, new ChildB()));
			........
			suite.addTest(new MyTest(&quot;testN&quot;, new ChildB()));
			return suite;
		}
		  public static void main(String[] args)
		  {
		    junit.swingui.TestRunner.run(MyTestClient.class);	
		  }	
	}

How I would like to write the suite method is something like this:

	public static Test suite()
	{
		TestSuite suite = new TestSuite();

		suite.addTest(MyTest.class /** Parameter here to indicate I
want to test ChildA */)
		suite.addTest(MyTest.class /** Parameter here to indicate I
want to test ChildB */)
	}

Hope this is a sensible question!

James
